verbose_text: With comparison of DCCT baseline characteristics of these 732 subjects with the remaining DCCT cohort (n = 563), duration of diabetes was shorter among those included (5.5 vs. 6.1 years, P value 0.016) and baseline HbA 1c levels were lower (8.76% [72 mmol / mol] vs. 9.01% [75 mmol / mol], P value 0.017).
